Hello,
I'm teaching (basic) functional programming and (simple) compilation in oca=
ml (to master students). Currently, I ask the system administrators to inst=
all a basic ocaml package. I'm thinking on switching to opam to make it eas=
ier for students to experiment various libraries.
=20
Does anyone has used opam for labs with student? I would be glad to hear an=
y report on this mainly on the following points:
- Is opam really usable when you keep changing of machine?
- Having a .opam for all student accounts seem interesting so that they can=
 freely experiment without interfering with others but has the cost of dupl=
icating lot of common files. Any thoughts?
- What is the usual size of an .opam directory? Mine is 1G but I don't know=
 if it's usual.
- What kind of ocaml libs do you introduce to the students? I was thinking =
of utop, ounit, core / batteries, menhir.=20

Thanks in advance
Fabien

